headline: Voters in Taiwan  Are Likely to Defy  Calls by Beijing For Unification
abstract: President Tsai Ing-wen’s prospects in the vote Saturday have been buoyed by a stronger economy and her promises to stand up to China.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Voters in Taiwan are widely expected to deliver a victory on Saturday to President Tsai Ing-wen, in defiance of China’s pressure campaign against the island democracy.
